        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 25 at 6:47PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 647 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles north of Kiowa, or 30 miles southeast of Denver, moving
northeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Bennett and Strasburg.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
